section.section:
In conjunction with the State Board of Morticians and Funeral Directors, the Director shall:
establish a process for regulating crematories that provides for:
registration of crematory operators or issuance of permits for operating crematories, and renewal;
applications, including certification of ownership and identification of individuals who will perform cremation;
registration and permit fees;
inspections and oversight;
grounds for discipline and penalties; and
complaints and hearings; and
adopt regulations that are identical to regulations adopted by the State Board of Morticians and Funeral Directors to:
implement item (i) of this paragraph; and
ensure public health and safety.
